introduction to the team
the data science group is made up of team member with diverse skill set across math and engineering dedicated to solving some of the most analytically challenging problem here at wayfair the work we do encompasses
data mining
- uncover deep insight hidden in our vast repository of raw data and provide tactical guidance on how act on finding
algorithm design
- develop quantitative model leveraging machine learning and advanced data analysis technique
algorithm platform engineering
- architect and build technical platform for our algorithmic engine to run at scale
influencing business decision
- relentlessly leverage our work and encourage adoption across our business partner to drive real business value
as part of this role you will be a creative thinker in how to solve problem utilizing quantitative technical skill along with business understanding to devise solution youll work within wayfairs big data technology infrastructure in order to dive deep into our data set and develop innovative new capability
the data science department cover three main topic area you will work in one of the following
data science personalization
build sophisticated platform designed to personalize customer experience to million of unique shopper across site and email this includes working on different type of recommendation engine a well a algorithm that machine-learn complex shopping behavior the goal is to be intelligent and automated in making the experience more relevant for every user
data science marketing
build the framework and algorithm that help guide wayfairs 250m+ annual marketing investment the work touch all marketing channel tv catalog and digital and aim to improve our ability to measure marketing impact improve our customer targeting and optimize our investment across million of marketing campaign
data science operations
build data-driven solution to support wayfair operation team including merchandising operations b2b supplier performance and customer service the big goal are to enhance wayfairs behind-the-scenes operational capability through rigorous use of algorithm and analysis
responsibilities
partner closely with business lead in marketing product or operations to plan out valuable data science project
work in complex data system and wrangle data from multiple source including sale customer and clickstream database
conduct analysis and build model to uncover key learning from data leading to appropriate strategy recommendation
serve a an algorithm and engineering lead to build advanced quantitative solution into our overall technical platform
work alongside business stakeholder to apply our finding and development and continually improve the wayfair customer experience
qualifications
2+ year of experience in a quantitative or technical work environment or advanced degree
phd
or ma ms in quantitative field eg mathematics economics operation research etc
intuitive sense of how quantitative and technical work aligns closely with business priority and business value
ability to effectively work with business lead strong communication skill ability to synthesize conclusion for non-experts and desire to influence business decision
high comfort level with programming eg language such a sql python r scala java c++ c php etc
knowledge of quantitative method statistic machine learning general data analysis
intense intellectual curiosity strong desire to always be learning
analytical creative and innovative approach to solving open-ended problem
highly collaborative team-player attitude
